#10)

R=25
teta= 10 #grados
d=R/2
ar1 <- function(R,teta){
  result <- (((pi*(R^2))*teta)/360)
  return(result)
}
area1 <- ar1(R,teta)
area1
## [1] 54.54154
ar2 <- function(d,R){
  result2 <- (sqrt(R^2 - d^2))
  return(result2)
}
area2 <-ar2(d,R)
area2
## [1] 21.65064
ar_final <- area1 - area2
ar_final
## [1] 32.8909

funcion<-9.87*sin(2*y)-7.35*cos(y)-1.5*sin(y)
n<-month.abb
n<-x/33.27
